// CVX 164 (Meningococcal B, NOS) is not listed in the table above because it does not count toward the completion of the Meningococcal B series. CVX 164 is categorized in the "Other Vaccine Group". 
// (Reference the General Rules for more details.) If CVX 164 is reported, then evaluate as NOT_EVALUATED (new evaluation code) and the reason code is VACCINE_NOT_SUPPORTED (new reason code). Ignore
// he reported CVX 164 when determining the recommended vaccine and calculating the recommended due date for the next target dose. 
//
// AI: Confirm if this should be displayed in the Meningococcal B vaccine group, or the Other Vaccine Group


/*************************************************************************************************************************************************************************************
MenB FHbp 2-dose Series specific rules
*************************************************************************************************************************************************************************************/

// If CVX 163 (Meningococcal B 4C, OMV (Bexsero)) is reported in Men B FHbp 2-dose series, evaluate as Accepted and the reason code is VACCINE_NOT_COUNTED_BASED_ON_MOST_RECENT_VACCINE_GIVEN.
// Ignore the reported CVX 163 when determining the recommended vaccine and calculating the recommended due date for the next target dose.
rule "Mening B / FHbp 2-dose series: Evaluate CVX 163 as ACCEPTED/VACCINE_NOT_COUNTED_BASED_ON_MOST_RECENT_VACCINE_GIVEN and ignore shot" ruleflow-group "HistoryEvaluation"
	dialect "mvel"
	agenda-group "customEvaluationRule"
	activation-group "allowableVaccineCheck"
	when
		There is an administered shot $currentShot that needs to be evaluated
			- the shot belongs to the Vaccine Group "VACCINE_GROUP_CONCEPT.850"	and the Series with name "MenBFHbp2DoseSeries"
			- the vaccine administered is "ICE163"
			- make note of the associated series as $targetSeries
	then
		Mark the shot $currentShot as Accepted for this Series due to "Vaccine Not Counted Based on Most Recent Vaccine Given"
		Mark the shot $currentShot as Ignored
		Record that this dose rule was Processed for the TargetDose $currentShot
		Log that this dose rule fired for the dose $currentShot in the Series $targetSeries
end

/*************************************************************************************************************************************************************************************
MenB FHbp 2-dose Series specific rules END
*************************************************************************************************************************************************************************************/


/*************************************************************************************************************************************************************************************
MenB FHbp 3-dose Series specific rules
*************************************************************************************************************************************************************************************/

// Absolute minimum interval between Dose 1 and Dose 3o in Men B FHbp 3-dose series is 6 months minus 4 days
rule "Mening B / FHbp 3-dose series: Evaluate the Absolute Minimum Interval in MenB FHbp 3-dose Series between Doses 1 and 3 as 6m-4d" ruleflow-group "HistoryEvaluation"
	dialect "mvel"
	agenda-group "customEvaluationRule"
	when  
		There is an Administered Shot $currentShot that needs to be evaluated
			- the shot belongs to the Vaccine Group "VACCINE_GROUP_CONCEPT.850"
			- the dose number in the series is == 3
			- make note of the date this shot was administered as $dtAdministrationDateCurrentShot
		There is an Administered Shot $previousDose
			- the shot belongs to the Vaccine Group "VACCINE_GROUP_CONCEPT.850"
			- the dose number in the series is == 1
		- that has already been evaluated and whose shot validity is VALID
			- make note of the date this shot was administered as $dtAdministrationDatePreviousDose
		There is a Series $targetSeries that contains the Dose $currentDose
			- the Series also contains the Dose $previousDose
			- the Series belongs to the Vaccine Group "VACCINE_GROUP_CONCEPT.850"
			- the name of the Series is "MenBFHbp3DoseSeries"
		Confirm Elapsed time between $dtAdministrationDatePreviousDose and $dtAdministrationDateCurrentDose < "6m-4d"
	then
		Mark the shot $currentDose as Invalid for this Series due to "Below Minimum Interval"
		Record that this dose rule was Processed for the TargetDose $currentDose
		Log that this dose rule fired for the dose $currentDose in the Series $targetSeries
end

